BRIEFLY 
Ex-Disney Exec Pleads Guilty: A former Walt Disney Co. executive pleaded guilty 
to tax evasion charges for taking tens of thousands of dollars and a gold Rolex 
watch as kickbacks from foreign souvenir suppliers. Geoffrey G. Gleed, 52, of 
Anaheim, ex-vice president of purchasing for Disney, pleaded guilty to two 
counts of tax evasion for not declaring money he received from Kanzo Itoh &amp; 
Co. of Japan and Kutex International Ltd. of Hong Kong, prosecutors said. 
